# CareerOS Campus AI — Project Rules

## What this project is

Intel-optimized placement-readiness operating layer for Indian colleges.
Demo loop: resumes in → ATS-safe + JD-matched + proof-linked scoring out →
student fixes + placement-officer cohort dashboard → Intel benchmark panel.

NOT: a job board, LinkedIn scraper, recruiter platform, or billing product.

## Startup — execute before every response (every chat)

1. Read `.obsidian-ai-memory/02-PROJECTS/session-continuity.md` — rolling handoff
2. Read `.obsidian-ai-memory/02-PROJECTS/project-context.md`
3. Read `.obsidian-ai-memory/02-PROJECTS/active-goals.md`
4. Read `.obsidian-ai-memory/03-ERRORS/error-memory.md`
5. Read `.obsidian-ai-memory/03-ERRORS/anti-patterns.md`
6. Read latest session digest(s) from `01-SESSIONS/` (see continuity file)
7. Emit startup block, then work

Cursor shutdown: `.cursor/MEMORY-WORKFLOW.md` (code commit → memory commit → push) | Cross-tool: `MEMORY-WRITE-PROTOCOL.md`

## Non-negotiable rules

- Read memory before every response or edit
- Never repeat known errors (check `03-ERRORS/error-memory.md` first)
- Never expose secrets — no JWT secrets, DB passwords, API keys in any file
- Verify before "done": `tsc --noEmit` clean (apps/web) + Python AST-parse clean (services/*)
- No fabrication in `services/ai-rewriter` — unsupported claims go in `unsupported_claims[]`
- PlacementReadinessScore formula lives in `packages/scoring/` only — never duplicated
- Confirm before destructive ops: `rm`, `DROP TABLE`, force push, `git reset --hard`, Alembic on live DB
- One concern per commit; no WIP commits on `main`
- Update docs when behaviour changes
- **End of every Cursor chat:** session digest + update `session-continuity.md` + commit vault (`memory:`) — see `.cursor/rules/memory-session.mdc`

## Current-week focus

Always check `.obsidian-ai-memory/02-PROJECTS/active-goals.md` for the active week.
Do not jump ahead to later-week tasks unless the user explicitly asks.

Full rules: `AGENTS.md` · `AI_RULES.md` · `STARTUP_PROTOCOL.md`
